                  <persName id="t18220220-196-person1765">
                  RICHARD 
                  HUGHES
               <interp inst="t18220220-196-person1765" type="surname" value="HUGHES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220220-196-person1765" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220220-196-person1765" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was going to Shadwell, with a load of hay, and asked the prisoner the way; my young master was with me - we had unloaded our hay, and were coming home, when the prisoner took my coat out of the cart; a boy told me of it. The officer pursued and took him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220220-196-person1766">GEORGE. MARTIN</persName>
            . I am servant to Mr. Hart, of Shadwell. I saw the prisoner take the coat out of the cart, and run across the fields. I told the officer, and he pursued, and took. I am sure he is the man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220220-196-person1767">
                  THOMAS 
                  AMOS
               <interp inst="t18220220-196-person1767" type="surname" value="AMOS"></interp>
